# BYO OAuth ergonomics (spec §7): `gum auth login` and the `gum login` alias
# run the loopback + PKCE flow against the operator's own OAuth client — no
# gcloud, and no mandatory --scope (it defaults to the full catalog scope set).
# The managed gum_oauth client takes over automatically once its scopes pass
# Google verification.
#
# These assertions use --help so they stay deterministic regardless of the
# host keychain state (the OS keyring is not sandboxed by HOME).

# The top-level `gum login` alias is registered.
gum login --help
stdout 'Authorize gum'

# `gum auth login` advertises the no-gcloud BYO loopback flow.
gum auth login --help
stdout 'loopback'

# --scope is optional: the login defaults to the core Workspace scope set, with
# --service / --all for the breadth catalog. The help must NOT demand an
# explicit scope the way the old managed flow did.
stdout '--scope'
stdout '--service'
stdout '--all'
! stdout 'at least one --scope is required'
